Manufacturer/Designer

Each choice gives certain bonuses/maluses.
* Avro
  + reduced weight penalty for big/strong bomb bay
  - cost slightly higher
* Bristol
  + better man≈ìuvrability
* de Havilland
  + sleek fuselages
* Handley Page
* Short Bros
  + cost is less sensitive to size
  - increased tare
* Supermarine
  + extra speed
  - slower development
  "Supermarine are the experts in high-speed aviation.  But their development times are not so quick."
* Vickers/Armstrongs

Data

Armstrongs
: wing arpen goes down to 6.0 instead of 8.0
: -20% mounting weight for Armstrong-Siddeley engines
: -10% tare for FuseType.SLABBY
Avro
: bomb bay
:: -8% for BBGirth.COOKIE
:: factor base +1000
: +5% to airframe cost (i.e. excl engines, turrets)
Bristol
: -20% mounting weight for Bristol engines
: turn penalty for wing loading starts at 18 instead of 16
dH
: -10% drag for FuseType.NORMAL
: +10% tare for FuseType.NORMAL
HP
: no specials at all?
: hidden flaws (rudder)
Shorts
: +8% to core/fuse tare
: -20% to core/fuse cost
: 0.9 power scaling of wing cost
: -15pp to serviceability
Supermarine
: +5% to wing L/D
: -10% to fuse drag
Vickers
: allows FuseType.GEODETIC
